trans-unit.source: Contains methods, properties, and events to support navigation.
trans-unit.target: Contém métodos, propriedades e eventos para oferecer suporte à navegação.

trans-unit.source: NavigationService encapsulates the ability to download content within the context of a browser-style navigation.
trans-unit.target: NavigationService encapsula a capacidade de baixar o conteúdo dentro do contexto de navegação de um estilo de navegador.

trans-unit.source: Content can be any type of [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winfx](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-winfx-md.md)] object and [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_html](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-html-md.md)] files.
trans-unit.target: O conteúdo pode ser qualquer tipo de [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winfx](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-winfx-md.md)] objeto e [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_html](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-html-md.md)] arquivos.

trans-unit.source: In general, however, pages are the preferred as the way to package content for navigation (see <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>).
trans-unit.target: Em geral, no entanto, páginas são preferenciais como o modo de conteúdo do pacote para navegação (consulte <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>).</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>

trans-unit.source: Content can be navigated to by providing an instance of an object and calling an overload of the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> method that accepts an object: - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> Alternatively, content can be navigated to by passing a relative or absolute [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] to one of the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> method overloads that accepts a [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)]: - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%29?displayProperty=fullName> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%2CSystem.Boolean%29?displayProperty=fullName> When content is navigated to by [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)], NavigationService will return an object that contains the content.
trans-unit.target: Conteúdo pode ser navegado, fornecendo uma instância de um objeto e chamar uma sobrecarga o <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>método que aceita um objeto:- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName>como alternativa, o conteúdo pode ser navegada passando relativo ou absoluto [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] para um do <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>sobrecargas do método que aceita um [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)]:- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%29?displayProperty=fullName>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%2CSystem.Boolean%29?displayProperty=fullName>ao conteúdo é navegado por [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)], NavigationService retornará um objeto que contém o conteúdo.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%2CSystem.Boolean%29?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%29?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>

trans-unit.source: The lifetime of a navigation can be tracked through the following events: - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigating> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigated> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationProgress> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationFailed> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.LoadCompleted> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.FragmentNavigation>.
trans-unit.target: O tempo de vida de uma navegação pode ser controlado por meio de eventos a seguir:- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigating>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigated>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationProgress>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationFailed>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.LoadCompleted>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.FragmentNavigation>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.FragmentNavigation> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.LoadCompleted> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationFailed> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationProgress> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigated> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigating>

trans-unit.source: Not all events are raised each time that a navigation occurs; the set of events that are raised is determined by the type of navigation that occurs (content or content fragment) and how the navigation completes (canceled, stopped, or failed).
trans-unit.target: Nem todos os eventos são gerados sempre que ocorra uma navegação; o conjunto de eventos que são gerados é determinado pelo tipo de navegação que ocorre (fragmento de conteúdo ou conteúdo) e como a navegação é concluída (cancelada, interrompido ou falha).

trans-unit.source: The following figure illustrates the sequence in which these events are raised: ![Page navigation flow chart](~/add/media/navigationoverviewfigure11.png "Page navigation flow chart") During or after a navigation, NavigationService provides information about the content that is being navigated to, including the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] of the content being navigated to (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Source%2A>), the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] of the current content (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CurrentSource%2A>), and an object that contains the content that was navigated to (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A>).
trans-unit.target: A figura a seguir ilustra a sequência na qual esses eventos são gerados: ![gráfico de fluxo de navegação de página](~/add/media/navigationoverviewfigure11.png "gráfico de fluxo de navegação de página") durante ou após uma navegação, NavigationService fornece informações sobre o conteúdo que está sendo navegado, incluindo o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] do conteúdo que está sendo navegado (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Source%2A>), o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] do conteúdo atual (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CurrentSource%2A>) e um objeto que contém o conteúdo que foi direcionado (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A>).</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CurrentSource%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Source%2A>

trans-unit.source: When content is navigated to, NavigationService records the navigation as an entry in navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Quando o conteúdo é navegar até, NavigationService registra a navegação como uma entrada no histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: An entry is added to back navigation history when either a new navigation occurs, by calling the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> method, or by navigating to an entry in forward navigation history, by calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Uma entrada é adicionada para fazer o histórico de navegação quando ocorre uma nova navegação, chamando o <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>método, ou navegando para uma entrada no histórico de navegação de avanço, chamando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>

trans-unit.source: An entry is added to forward navigation history by navigating to an entry in back navigation history, by calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Uma entrada é adicionada ao histórico de navegação de avanço, navegando para uma entrada no histórico de navegação, chamando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoBack%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoForward%2A> report whether there are entries in back and forward navigation history, respectively.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoBack%2A>e <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoForward%2A>relatar se há entradas no e o histórico de navegação de avanço, respectivamente.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoForward%2A></xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoBack%2A>

trans-unit.source: Also, the most recent entry in back navigation history can be removed by calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.RemoveBackEntry%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Além disso, é possível remover a entrada mais recente no histórico de navegação chamando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.RemoveBackEntry%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.RemoveBackEntry%2A>

trans-unit.source: By default, NavigationService does not store an instance of a content object in navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Por padrão, NavigationService não armazena uma instância de um objeto de conteúdo no histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: Instead, NavigationService creates a new instance of the content object each time it is navigated to by using navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Em vez disso, NavigationService cria uma nova instância do objeto conteúdo de cada vez que ele é para onde navegar usando o histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: This behavior is designed to avoid excessive memory consumption when large numbers and large pieces of content are being navigated to.
trans-unit.target: Esse comportamento é projetado para evitar o consumo excessivo de memória quando grandes números e grandes partes do conteúdo estão sendo navegados.

trans-unit.source: Consequently, the state of the content is not remembered from one navigation to the next.
trans-unit.target: Consequentemente, o estado do conteúdo não será lembrado na barra de uma navegação para a próxima.

trans-unit.source: However, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] provides several techniques by which you can store a piece of state for a piece of content in navigation history.
trans-unit.target: No entanto, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] oferece várias técnicas que você pode armazenar uma parte do estado de uma parte do conteúdo no histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: Using <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.AddBackEntry%2A>, you can also remember multiple sets of state for a single page instance.
trans-unit.target: Usando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.AddBackEntry%2A>, lembre-se também vários conjuntos de estado para uma instância única página.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.AddBackEntry%2A>

trans-unit.source: NavigationService is `sealed` class and, therefore, cannot be instantiated; instead, NavigationService is used by navigators to enable navigation.
trans-unit.target: NavigationService é `sealed` classe e, portanto, não pode ser instanciado; em vez disso, NavigationService é usado por navegadores para permitir a navegação.

trans-unit.source: In [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)], there are two navigators: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.
trans-unit.target: Em [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)], há dois navegadores: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: Visually, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] use [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] as a navigator, to provide an integrated user experience.
trans-unit.target: Visualmente, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] usar [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] como um navegador, para fornecer uma experiência de usuário integrada.

trans-unit.source: Physically, however, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] actually use <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> as the navigator; the <xref:System.Windows.Application.MainWindow%2A> property of an [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] running in [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] will return a reference to the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, and the navigation history that is managed by the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> is integrated with the navigation history that is managed by [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] in the following ways: - When content is navigated to by calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A>, and <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A> from within an [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] the relevant navigation history entries are also added to [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Fisicamente, no entanto, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] realmente usa <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>como o navegador; o <xref:System.Windows.Application.MainWindow%2A>propriedade de um [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] em execução no [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] retornará uma referência ao <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>e o histórico de navegação que é gerenciado pelo <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>é integrado com o histórico de navegação que é gerenciado pelo [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] das seguintes maneiras: - quando o conteúdo é direcionado ao chamar <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A>, e <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A>de dentro um [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] as entradas de histórico de navegação relevantes também são adicionadas ao [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] histórico de navegação.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> </xref:System.Windows.Application.MainWindow%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: - When entries in the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] navigation [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] are selected, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] causes NavigationService to navigate back or forwards to the content that is associated with those entries.
trans-unit.target: -Quando entradas na [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] navegação [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] forem selecionadas, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] faz com que o NavigationService navegar de volta ou encaminha para o conteúdo que está associado essas entradas.

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > A <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> can provide its own navigation history, or use the navigation history of the navigator that hosts it.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Um <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>pode fornecer seu próprio histórico de navegação, ou usar o histórico de navegação do navegador que hospeda o proprietário.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> provides its own navigation history, it can display its own navigation [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] to navigate through the entries in navigation history; those entries are not added to the navigation history of the host navigator (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_iegeneric](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-iegeneric-md.md)]) and, consequently, cannot be navigated to from the navigation [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] of each (see <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame.JournalOwnership%2A>).
trans-unit.target: Se <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>fornece seu próprio histórico de navegação, ele pode exibir sua própria navegação [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] para navegar por meio de entradas no histórico de navegação; essas entradas não são adicionadas ao histórico de navegação do navegador de host (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_iegeneric](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-iegeneric-md.md)]) e, consequentemente, não pode ser acessada de painel de navegação [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] de cada (consulte <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame.JournalOwnership%2A>).</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame.JournalOwnership%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>

trans-unit.source: Since navigations are asynchronous, it is possible for multiple navigations to be in progress at the same time.
trans-unit.target: Como navegações são assíncronas, é possível que várias navegações para estar em andamento ao mesmo tempo.

trans-unit.source: For example, if there are two child frames on a single page, both frames could be navigating.
trans-unit.target: Por exemplo, se houver dois quadros filho em uma única página, ambos os quadros podem navegar.

trans-unit.source: In this case, the various navigation events that are raised by <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService> may be raised multiple times, one for each piece of content that is being navigated to, and not necessarily in order that the navigations were requested.
trans-unit.target: Nesse caso, os vários eventos de navegação que são gerados pelo <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>pode ser gerada várias vezes, uma para cada parte do conteúdo que está sendo navegado, e não necessariamente para que as navegações foram solicitadas.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>

trans-unit.source: Consequently, if a particular navigation request needs to process data that is specific to the individual request, it cannot use data that is available to all navigation requests.
trans-unit.target: Consequentemente, se precisar de uma solicitação de navegação específico processar os dados que são específicos para a solicitação individual, ele não pode usar dados que estão disponíveis para todas as solicitações de navegação.

trans-unit.source: Instead, you can use `navigationState` to pass data for navigation processing that is specific to one navigation request.
trans-unit.target: Em vez disso, você pode usar `navigationState` para passar dados para navegação de processamento que é específica para a solicitação de navegação de um.

trans-unit.target: Lidar com navegação se você precisar descobrir informações pertinentes sobre a solicitação de navegação antes do início da navegação.

trans-unit.source: This information is available from the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigatingCancelEventArgs> object that is passed to the Navigating event handler.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Net.WebRequest> object for the navigation is created and available from the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigatingCancelEventArgs> parameter; because the actual request hasn't been made at this point, you can reconfigure the <xref:System.Net.WebRequest> object, if necessary.
trans-unit.target: Um <xref:System.Net.WebRequest>do objeto para a navegação é criado e está disponível na <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigatingCancelEventArgs>parâmetro; porque a solicitação real ainda não foram feita neste ponto, você pode reconfigurar o <xref:System.Net.WebRequest>do objeto, se necessário.</xref:System.Net.WebRequest> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigatingCancelEventArgs> </xref:System.Net.WebRequest>

trans-unit.source: You also handle <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigatingCancelEventArgs> to cancel navigation, if required, by setting <xref:System.ComponentModel.CancelEventArgs.Cancel%2A> to true.
trans-unit.target: Você também tratar <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigatingCancelEventArgs>para cancelar a navegação, se necessário, definindo <xref:System.ComponentModel.CancelEventArgs.Cancel%2A>como true.</xref:System.ComponentModel.CancelEventArgs.Cancel%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigatingCancelEventArgs>

trans-unit.source: If you cancel navigation, no other navigation events are raised.
trans-unit.target: Se você cancelar a navegação, nenhum outro evento de navegação é gerado.

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > If your application is hosted in the browser, you cannot prevent the user from navigating away from your application by canceling the Navigating event.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Se seu aplicativo for hospedado no navegador, você não pode impedir que o usuário navegar para fora de seu aplicativo ao cancelar o evento de navegação.

trans-unit.source: After the first piece of content is navigated to by a navigator (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>), each piece of content that is navigated away from is added to navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Depois que a primeira parte do conteúdo é navegada por um navegador (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>), cada parte do conteúdo é navegado para fora é adicionado ao histórico de navegação.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: If you need to save state information about the content you are navigating away from, you can add the state to the journal entry for that content by setting <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigatingCancelEventArgs.ContentStateToSave%2A> with a <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.CustomContentState> object.
trans-unit.target: Se você precisar salvar informações de estado sobre o conteúdo que você está navegando longe do, você pode adicionar o estado para a entrada do diário para esse conteúdo definindo <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigatingCancelEventArgs.ContentStateToSave%2A>com um <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.CustomContentState>objeto.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.CustomContentState> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigatingCancelEventArgs.ContentStateToSave%2A>

trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Quando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>gera navegando, ele também gera <xref:System.Windows.Application.Navigating?displayProperty=fullName>evento no <xref:System.Windows.Application>objeto.</xref:System.Windows.Application> </xref:System.Windows.Application.Navigating?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>

trans-unit.target: Quando tanto um <xref:System.Net.WebException>ou um <xref:System.IO.IOException>é lançada durante a navegação, o evento é gerado de NavigationFailed.</xref:System.IO.IOException> </xref:System.Net.WebException>

trans-unit.source: NavigationFailed is passed a <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationFailedEventArgs> that encapsulates information about both the exception and the details of the navigation that caused the exception.
trans-unit.target: NavigationFailed é passado um <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationFailedEventArgs>que encapsula informações sobre a exceção e os detalhes do painel de navegação que causou a exceção.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationFailedEventArgs>

trans-unit.source: When an exception results from a failed navigation, and is unhandled, the following events are raised in the order listed: - NavigationFailed.
trans-unit.target: Quando uma exceção resulta de uma falha na navegação e é sem tratamento, os seguintes eventos são gerados na ordem listada:-NavigationFailed.

trans-unit.source: - <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame.NavigationFailed?displayProperty=fullName> or <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationFailed?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: - <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame.NavigationFailed?displayProperty=fullName> or <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationFailed?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationFailed?displayProperty=fullName></xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame.NavigationFailed?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: - <xref:System.Windows.Application.NavigationFailed?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: - <xref:System.Windows.Application.NavigationFailed?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Windows.Application.NavigationFailed?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: Occurs periodically during a download to provide navigation progress information.
trans-unit.target: Ocorre periodicamente durante um download para fornecer informações de andamento de navegação.

trans-unit.source: NavigationProgress is passed a <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs> which exposes the following progress information: - Number of bytes downloaded so far (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A>).
trans-unit.target: NavigationProgress é passado um <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs>que expõe as seguintes informações de progresso:-número de bytes baixados até o momento (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A>).</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs>

trans-unit.source: - Number of total bytes to download (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A>).
trans-unit.target: -Número total de bytes para download (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A>).</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A>

trans-unit.source: NavigationProgress is raised once for every 1024 bytes of content downloaded, and once more if the number of remaining bytes is ever less than 1024 bytes.
trans-unit.target: NavigationProgress é gerado uma vez para cada 1024 bytes do conteúdo baixado e mais uma vez se o número de bytes restantes é sempre menor que 1024 bytes.

trans-unit.source: For this reason, handling NavigationProgress provides a useful way to track and display the progress of a current download.
trans-unit.target: Por esse motivo, a manipulação NavigationProgress fornece uma maneira útil de controlar e exibir o andamento de um download atual.

trans-unit.source: NavigationProgress won't be raised in some cases, such as when the same piece of content is navigated to, or when a content fragment is navigated to on content that is currently loaded (that is, the value of the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A> property).
trans-unit.target: NavigationProgress não ser gerado em alguns casos, como quando a mesma parte do conteúdo é direcionada, ou quando um fragmento de conteúdo é para onde navegar no conteúdo que está atualmente carregado (ou seja, o valor da <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A>propriedade).</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A>

trans-unit.source: When navigating to a compiled XAML resource, the final NavigationProgress event may not be raised.
trans-unit.target: Ao navegar para um recurso XAML compilado, o evento NavigationProgress final não poderá ser gerado.

trans-unit.source: This means that at the end of the download, the last reported <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A> value may not equal the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A> value.
trans-unit.target: Isso significa que, ao final do download, o último relatado <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A>valor não pode ser igual a <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A>valor.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A>

trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Quando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>gera NavigationProgress, ele também gera <xref:System.Windows.Application.NavigationProgress?displayProperty=fullName>evento sobre o <xref:System.Windows.Application>objeto.</xref:System.Windows.Application> </xref:System.Windows.Application.NavigationProgress?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>

trans-unit.target: -Dados adicionais, se a navegação foi iniciada chamando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A?displayProperty=fullName>ou <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.target: Observe que, se o conteúdo atual é direcionado novamente, ao chamar <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>ou atualização, uma nova entrada não é adicionada ao histórico de navegação.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>

trans-unit.target: Se dois ou mais navegadores (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>) compartilham o mesmo histórico de navegação, um navegador pode usar RemoveBackEntry para recuperar a entrada do histórico de navegação para uma navegação que ocorreu em outro navegador.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: The most recent <xref href="System.Windows.Navigation.JournalEntry"></xref> in back navigation history, if there is one.
trans-unit.target: O mais recente <xref href="System.Windows.Navigation.JournalEntry"> </xref> no histórico de navegação, se houver um.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] of the current content, or the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] of new content that is currently being navigated to.
trans-unit.target: Obtém ou define o [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] o conteúdo atual, ou o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] conteúdo novo que está atualmente sendo navegado.

trans-unit.source: If you set this property to a different [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] than the one currently being displayed, the navigator (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>) navigates to the specified [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)].
trans-unit.target: Se você definir essa propriedade para outro [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] daquela que está sendo exibido no momento, o navegador (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>) navega especificado [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)].</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: Source is set to the content that is loaded from the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] that is navigated to, unless the navigation is canceled.
trans-unit.target: Origem será definida como o conteúdo carregado a partir de [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] que é direcionada, a menos que a navegação é cancelada.

trans-unit.source: Source can be set with a fragment-only [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)], and can be set to `null`.
trans-unit.target: Origem pode ser definida com um fragmento somente [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)]e pode ser definido como `null`.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Uri> that contains the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] for the current content, or the content that is currently being navigated to.
trans-unit.target: Um <xref:System.Uri>que contém o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] para o conteúdo atual ou o conteúdo que está atualmente sendo navegado.</xref:System.Uri>

trans-unit.source: Stops further downloading of content for the current navigation request.
trans-unit.target: Interrompe mais download de conteúdo para a solicitação de navegação atual.

trans-unit.source: StopLoading can be called as soon as <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> returns, and stops navigation that is in progress in child frames.
trans-unit.target: Pode ser chamado StopLoading assim <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>retorna e deixa de navegação que está em andamento em quadros filho.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>

trans-unit.source: (<xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>).
trans-unit.target: (<xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>).</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>

trans-unit.source: Calling the StopLoading method raises the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped> event.
trans-unit.target: Chamar o método StopLoading gera o <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped>evento.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > StopLoading must be called on the same thread that initiated the navigation.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > StopLoading deve ser chamado no mesmo thread que iniciou a navegação.
